premise_source_doc_sentence: John Dall  (  May 26 , 1920 -- January 15 , 1971  )  was an American actor .

Primarily a stage actor , he is best remembered today for two film roles : the cool-minded intellectual killer in Alfred Hitchcock 's Rope  (  1948  )  , and the trigger-happy lead in the 1950 noir Gun Crazy .
He also had a substantial role in Stanley Kubrick 's Spartacus  (  1960  )  .

He first came to fame as the young prodigy who comes alive under the tutelage of Bette Davis in The Corn Is Green  (  1945  )  , for which he was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor .
Warner Bros signed him to a contract to make the film , but they let him go in 1946 .

Starring James Stewart , John Dall and Farley Granger , this is the first of Hitchcock 's Technicolor films , and is notable for taking place in real time and being edited so as to appear as a single continuous shot through the use of long takes .
